item.title: ET66 Calculator
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: In the mid 1950s Braun and Dieter Rams introduced German modern industrial design into the common home and office. The design of the calculator can be seen making a cameo as the previous iPhone calculator. Its the perfectly minimal addition to the top of any desk. Battery included.

item.title: The new sound of home.
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded:
Stammen is neat and compact. But dont let size fool you. Packed with a subwoofer and two high-class tweeters, Stammen will treat your ears to a full sound experience. Great for small to mid-sized spaces, like living rooms, bedrooms, and studio apartments.
Connect to anything, play everything
These might very well be the best wireless speakers out there, 'cause they let you play your music however you want. Tune to your favorite music streaming services, use them as Bluetooth speakers, or grab an AUX cord and hook up the turntable.

item.title: Best drip coffee & supplies
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded:
When choosing your pour over method, think about the overall time that will go into making your coffee.<!--more--> Most pour-over methods will take about on average 3-5 minutes to brew your coffee and about 3-5 minutes to prepare the coffee after measuring, grinding, and boiling water. All in all, that's nearly 10 minutes dedicated to your brew. Make sure that you know how much time you want to dedicate to making coffee. Some need less time to brew, and some need more time to brew. If you subscribe to the BS mantra 'time is money', choosing the wrong brewer will-piss-you-right-off.
One small tip - avoid the Chemex if you're a rush individual.

item.title: Distracted? Focus.
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded:
The more our phones do, the more they demand of us. Sometimes its good to take a break. But until now, the only alternative to hyper-connected smartphones has been the kind of phone you find at the back of a drawer...

The Punkt. MP 01 is a stylish, well-crafted mobile phone which focuses on modern simplicity, inside and out. It makes phone calls and sends texts. Thats all.

item.title: There is a place people call paradise
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Monocle's Travel Guide to Miami covers the city design like no other. This guide will reveal the hidden gems in this great city such as windsurfing, swimming, jet-skiing, juice bars, art and fashion. This is a collection of the Monocle team's favorite places on the shoreline, from the city's relaxing activities for the day to the energetic nightlife. Aimed at people who do not want to be tourists but rather feel like locals when they travel, these are books for those who want to mix the classic with the contemporary, want to get beyond the cliches, and know they can get a feel for a city even if they only have a few days.

item.title: CONTROL / TAF Architects
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded:
The CONTROL lamp is a unique and playful lamp with references to hi-fi and industrial machinery.

The light and dimmer is controlled by a switch, referencing- volume controls, and is an inviting and simple way of interacting with the user. While designing the lamp, we were inspired by the idea of displaying the different lamp components on a serving plate almost as a still life. It was a pragmatic approach to making a lamp by the simplest means, a reduced design beyond reduction.

item.title: Cruiser
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Inspired with the first skateboards of the 60s, this vintage style wooden skateboard deck is hand shaped out of natural hardwood. It comes in two shapes straight cut tail and squash tail (67cm & 60cm accordingly). Available as complete mounted skateboards in either Ash, Walnut, Maple, or Oak. The boards have a see through spray-on grip to accent the woods grain and maintaining a solid grip.

item.title: e15 Stop Bookend
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer:Philipp Mainzer Maker:e15 Material: Bianco Carrara marble (White) | Nero Marquina marble (Black) Dimensions: 10 10 H10 cm (S) | 10 10 H17 cm (L) 4 4 H4 in.(S) | 4 4 H6.7 in. (L) Origin:Germany
item.excerpt:encoded: Each STOP is carved from a solid marble block, simply chamfered and oiled to emphasize the unique texture and quality of the stone. Available in two heights with a choice of white Carrara or black Marquina marble, allowing a range combinations and uses.

item.title: Timbre Table Bell
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer: Gen Suzuki Maker: Timbre Material: Zinc die-casting finished with black/white paint. Dimensions: 6.8 6.8 H6 cm Origin: Japan
item.excerpt:encoded: A modern table bell by Tokyo-based Timbre, whose creative line of products are aimed to enrich life using gentle sounds generated by subtle movements. Designed by Gen Suzuki, this uniquely-shaped bell has an interior mechanism made of die-cast zinc, and a non-skid silicone base weighted with steel for stability. Comes in black and white.

item.title: Ito Bindery Memo Block
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer/Maker: Ito Bindery Material: Paper sheets and recycled paperboard Dimensions: 10.7 10.7 4.3 cm S | 15 10.7 4.3 cm M | 25.7 7.5 4.3 cm L Origin: Japan
item.excerpt:encoded: These exquisite paper blocks, each containing 350 tear-off sheets, were created by Ito Bindery of Japan. The precision-cut edges and silky smooth surface makes these blocks perfect for taking notes, sketching out ideas, or any other purpose you can think of. Each block has a recycled paperboard base, providing stability and heft.

item.title: Adhesive Notes
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Material Paper Dimensions 2.1"W X 1"D X 0.2"H Weight 30g Origin Japan Designer CDT
item.excerpt:encoded: Craft Design Technology Adhesive Notes are adhesive sticky notes that come in white and pale green paper. The sticky notes are the appropriate size to use as bookmarks or for reminders.

item.title: Scissors
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Material Stainless Steel Dimensions 8.5"W X 3.9"D X 0.5"H Weight 182g Origin Japan Designer CDT
item.excerpt:encoded: These beautiful scissors are tuned like a fine Samurai sword. The scissors feature a universal design that is usable in both the right and left hand. Made from brushed stainless steel that produces a sharp edge for perfect cuts. This is manufactured by the traditional and heritage work of Sword artisans in Gifu prefecture, known for its sword production.

item.title: Pioneer of Swiss Graphic Design
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Year 1995 DimensionsH:1" x W: 7" x D: 10" MaterialsPaperback
item.excerpt:encoded: This illustrated essay traces the history of one of the leading exponents of " Swiss Graphic Design " in the 1950s and 1960s. Josef Mller-Brockmann's posters have become world famous for their ability to convey information with great visual tension, a sense of drama, and an extreme economy of means.

item.title: Standing Bowl
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Material Copper Dimensions 15"W X 6"D X 4"H Weight 5 lbs Origin Brooklyn Designer Fort Standard
item.excerpt:encoded: These sand cast aluminum bowls are coated in copper and elevated off the table surface by their architecturally inspired planar legs. The unique stance and food safe coating makes each bowl an ideal room center piece or kitchen fruit bowl. The copper coating is left unfinished so that it can develop a natural patina over time or maintain its shine through polishing. Sand cast in the state of Pennsylvania, food safe copper plating in Brooklyn, New York.

item.title: Boskke Cube
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Year 2013 DimensionsH:5.9" x W: 6.14" x D: 6.14"
item.excerpt:encoded: The Boskke Cube is a self-watering planter that is perfect for herbs and houseplants. Recommended for both green and brown thumbs, simply fill the cube with water and let the plant absorb the water through the terra-cotta base and have fresh herb ingredients for any meal. The large cube will hold a 4.5" plant and the small cube will hold a 3" plant.

item.title: 15 Minute Timer
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer / Maker: Polite Material: Glass Dimensions: 5.5 H13 cm Origin: United Kingdom
item.excerpt:encoded: A visual reminder to take a break during the day and carve out 15 minutes for what truly counts. That isn't very long, and that's the point: it's longer than we often give to so many of the things we ostensibly think of as so important like properly listening to a partner, rationally analyzing our career ambitions, or playing in a concentrated way with a child.

item.title: Endless Rain Record
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer: Kouichi Okamoto Maker: Kyouei Design Material: PVC and paper Dimensions: 32 x 32 cm Origin: Japan
item.excerpt:encoded: A vinyl phonograph record created by Japanese artist Kouichi Okamoto (a.k.a. Bekkou). This atmospheric record has circular grooves on its drop side, allowing the raindrop sounds to loop endlessly. The rain side includes a 10-minute track, featuring soothing sounds of a Summer rainfall. Each side is labeled with its respective Japanese character.

item.title: Tumbler Alarm Clock
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Material Steel Dimensions 3"W X 3"D X 3.8"H Weight 550g Origin Denmark Designer Norm Architects
item.excerpt:encoded: Tumbler is a modern variant of the classic alarm clock from Danish design duo, Norm Architects. With its rounded bottom and no-tilt design Norm's Tumbler alarm clock is decorative, practical, and fun to interact with. When it rings and wakes you up - you simply take the clock and turn it upside down to stop the alarm.

item.title: Minimalissimo Magazine
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer / Maker: Minimalissimo Material: 160 pages on 120gsm uncoated paper Dimensions: 21 27 cm Origin: United Kingdom
item.excerpt:encoded: 160 pages of editorial content organized under 5 categoriesarchitecture, art, fashion, graphic & package design, and industrial designfeaturing interviews with some of the leading creatives of today. The result is a collection of insightful articles and stunning visuals, celebrating the very best of minimalism in design.

item.title: Spacesuit
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Author:Nicholas de Monchaux Material: Hardcover book.380 pages, 26 color and114 b&w illustrations. Dimensions:18 23 cm | 7.1 9 in. Publisher: MIT Press Origin:United States
item.excerpt:encoded: The story of the Apollo spacesuit, the 21-layer garment that landed on the moon, told by Nicholas de Monchaux in 21 essays relevant to the suit, the body, and the technology of the twentieth century. He touches, among other things, on eighteenth-century androids, Christian Diors New Look, Atlas missiles, cybernetics and cyborgs, latex, JFK's carefully cultivated image, the CBS lunar broadcast soundstage, NASAs Mission Control, and the applications of Apollo-style engineering to city planning.

item.title: Playsam Streamliner Classic
item.dc:creator: TKDEMOS
item.content:encoded: Designer: Ulf Hanses Maker: Playsam Material: Solid Wood, high-gloss lacquer Dimensions: 13.5 7.5 6 cm Origin: Sweden Notes: Comes in a black cardboard gift box.
item.excerpt:encoded: Playsam is a Swedish design company known for its timeless, archetypal wooden toys. Their iconic product, the Streamliner Classic epitomizes Scandinavian Design with its use of material, simple construction, and minimalist aesthetic. This ageless toy is designed by Ulf Hanses and has been selected as a Design Classic by the Swedish National Museum of Fine Arts for its inventive style and high-gloss finish.
